column18: You are invited to participate in a research study conducted by Gobi Dasu, masters student at Stanford University. To be a participant in this study you must be at least 18 years of age or older.  Participation in this study is voluntary.  You will answer a few questions about consumer decisions.PURPOSE OF THE STUDY: We are investigating consumer decisions.PROCEDURES: You will be asked questions about consumer decisions. The survey will take approximately 6 minutes to complete.POTENTIAL RISKS AND DISCOMFORTS: There are no foreseeable physical or psychological risks associated with this study. POTENTIAL BENEFITS TO SUBJECTS AND/OR TO SOCIETY: There are no immediate benefits to participants. The data we collect from this study will contribute to ongoing research in consumer psychology.CONFIDENTIALITY: All responses are anonymous and no information that is obtained through your responses from this study will be identified with you.  Only the investigators will have access to your data during and after the study concludes.CONTACT INFORMATION: If you have any questions or concerns about this study, please feel free to contact Gobi Dasu gdasu@stanford.edu.RIGHTS OF RESEARCH SUBJECTS: Your participation in this study is voluntary. You may choose to withdraw consent and discontinue participation at any time without penalty. You are not waiving any legal claims, rights or remedies because of your participation in this research study. SIGNATURE OF RESEARCH SUBJECT: Your voluntary completion of the survey constitutes your consent to participate.  By continuing with the survey you signify that you understand the procedures described above and you agree to participate in this study.Do you consent to this process and wish to continue?
